OL,3,CHuge cost of bin strikes to the
OL,4,Cenvironment as recycling rates plummet
OL,6,FThat would mean roughly 161,000 tonnes
OL,7,Fof CO2 pumped into the atmosphere in
OL,8,Fthe first six months of the year alone
OL,9,F- the equivalent of driving 733
OL,10,Fmillion miles - or 29 and a half
OL,11,Fthousand trips around the world.
OL,13,F"At the moment, we're paying for all
OL,14,Fthe collection of what we don't want,
OL,15,Fand then we're paying for it to be
OL,16,Fburned and put in the sky," John added.
OL,18,F"So we've just had the hottest summer
OL,19,Fever recorded. Clearly, the sky is not
OL,20,Fable to take more or more of our
OL,21,Fwaste."
